sub_title: Fourth-year International Business Student at Saxion University of Applied Sciences
summary: Born in The Netherlands, gained work experience in the UK, Australia, and Czechia in various work environments. Result-driven individual with a newly found interest in Sustainability and Technology & Innovation. Over the years clients and peers have underlined my ability to work in a fast-paced environment as well as being a valuable team member with remarkable communication, problem-solving, and leadership skills.

projects:
[{'title': 'Research project - Automatization of data results from monetization via UTM links', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2023}}, 'description': 'Worked on a research project where the goal was to provide an implementation plan on how to create an automated process for monetization gained via UTM links. In this implementation plan the automation should ensure that the monetization is visualized automatically and that the data is accessible for each department. The automation and visualization had been done via Power BI. At the end of the project 3 items were delivered: A Power BI template on which the employees could build further, an explanatory video, and a step-by-step guide on how to create your own Power BI dashboard.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Melissa', 'last_name': 'Weel', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Fourth-year International Business Student at Saxion University of Applied Sciences'}]}, {'title': 'Smart Solutions Semester - Tinteling Romance', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, 'description': "In this semester a group of 8 interdisciplinary students (meaning from various educations within Saxion) were assigned a project to develop 'the book of the future' for the company Tinteling Romance. The goal was to create various prototype products for the client to use on short/mid/long term to create a competitive advantage.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Melissa', 'last_name': 'Weel', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Fourth-year International Business Student at Saxion University of Applied Sciences'}]}, {'title': 'Technology & Innovation - Business plan / implementation plan', 'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, 'description': "For the course Technology & Innovations students were tasked with creating a business plan and implementation plan for a project of their choice. The projects could go as far as actually going to the market. However,  due to multiple other projects running, my idea has not been brought to the market at the moment.  

 My innovative idea was called ''Smart Wardrobes'' and consisted of two products.
The first product is an app that would allow users to easily catalog their clothes in one place. Moreover, the app would be designed to allow users to find their clothes via their cameras. The app is made affordable for the masses through in-app advertisements. The second product was an expansion pack for the app and was a smart mirror where users could see their saved outfits on themselves in real-time.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Melissa', 'last_name': 'Weel', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Fourth-year International Business Student at Saxion University of Applied Sciences'}]}, {'title': 'Minor: Liberal Arts & Sciences', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, 'description': "During the minor Liberal Arts & Sciences 5 main topic areas are covered. The areas are called: Anthropology, Culture, Earth Sciences, Geopolitics & History, and Technology.

To test one's knowledge of these areas, various projects were put in place. For example, 3 essays had to be written with either 2 or more of the areas covered to see if students could explain how they are interconnected. For this project I wrote the following essays: 
- How would Germany have developed politically if the First World War never happened?
- Artificial ways to impact climate change
- How to make data objective and inclusive

If there is interest in reading any of the essays, feel free to reach out. 

One of the other projects was creating a product of choice which covers at least 4 of the 5 areas. For this project I decided to go with the following topic: 'Technology is the gateway towards achieving the four sustainability pillar goals'. The project was called 'The age of awareness' and is expressed through a website. The project follows how technology can be used in the various sustainability pillars and how it impacts the SDG goals.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Melissa', 'last_name': 'Weel', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Fourth-year International Business Student at Saxion University of Applied Sciences'}]}, {'title': 'Research project for WTC Twente - Online communities', 'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'The following research project contained an advice report for WTC Twente on the feasibility of creating an online community for their stakeholders', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Melissa', 'last_name': 'Weel', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Fourth-year International Business Student at Saxion University of Applied Sciences'}]}, {'title': 'All inclusive hospitality congress', 'date': {'start': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': 'During this Congress, there had been given the opportunity to enlighten yourself about working and being in the hospitality industry with a disability. This Congress has been an eye-opener for many under which I include myself. The term disability goes broader than one might think. Next to that, it became clear that if you want to be inclusive to people with a disability one must start with him/herself. 

A memorable quote from this congress was:
" Diversity is being invited to the party, inclusion is being asked to dance."
